    <p>
      Around this time, the company <a href="https://www.ust.cz/" target="_blank">Universal Scientific Technologies (UST)</a> was founded in connection with the development of MLAB. Initially, UST began manufacturing MLAB modules primarily for its own needs, but over time, it started providing them to other customers as well. This model continues to this day, supporting both internal projects and a wider user base.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Growing Community</h2>
    <p>
      Since its inception, MLAB has continuously evolved and expanded. Thanks to its openness and versatility, it has gained the support of a wide-ranging community of enthusiasts and professionals. This includes researchers from institutions of the Czech Academy of Sciences, hobbyist groups like <a href="https://www.robozor.cz/" target="_blank">Robozor</a>, and observation networks such as the meteor detection system <a href="https://www.bolidozor.cz/" target="_blank">Bolidozor</a>.
    </p>

