    <p>
      A significant milestone in MLAB’s growth was the transition from a self-hosted Subversion documentation server to 
      <a href="https://github.com/MLAB-project" target="_blank">GitHub</a>. For the electronic modules themselves, a separate GitHub organization, 
      <a href="https://github.com/MLAB-modules" target="_blank">MLAB-modules</a>, was established. This change allowed for seamless collaboration, enabling more contributors to get involved easily. Additionally, it played a crucial role in increasing awareness of 
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_hardware" target="_blank">open-source hardware</a> and fostering a more inclusive and engaged community.
    </p>
    <p>
      These communities have contributed their expertise, ideas, and innovations, making MLAB a platform for knowledge sharing and collaboration.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">MLAB Today</h2>
    <p>
      Today, MLAB is not only a tool for development and testing but also a resource for education and inspiration for a new generation of engineers and scientists. Its story continues with every new module, article, and project created and shared by the community.
    </p>


